Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-02T21:47:51.9335942Z [{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/1746","id":3618523973,"node_id":"PR_kwDOPUU0qc7XrktF","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1746","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1746.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1746.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1746","number":1746,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"fix(security): sanitize interactive-mode comments to plug Telegram bot token leak (#1745)","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n\nFixes #1745 — the Telegram bot token (`8490528355:AAGHe…HCY`, since revoked) leaked into a public PR comment because `interactive-mode.lib.mjs` posted raw `Bash`-tool stdout to GitHub via `gh api … --input -` without running it through output sanitization. The Telegram-token regex already existed; it was simply never invoked on the comment-publishing path.\n\nThis PR plugs the leak, broadens generated-output sanitization, adds static guardrails, adds operator tooling, and ships regression coverage.\n\n## Root cause\n\n- `src/interactive-mode.lib.mjs#postComment` and `editComment` published comment bodies verbatim.\n- The Telegram pattern (`/\\b[0-9]{8,10}:[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{30,}/g`) and `secretlint` were never wired into that codepath.\n- See `docs/case-studies/issue-1745/analysis.md` for the full timeline.\n\n## What changed\n\n**Defense layer 1 — output sanitization**\n- `src/token-sanitization.lib.mjs`: `sanitizeOutput()` is now the canonical sanitizer for generated outbound output. `sanitizeLogContent()` remains as a backward-compatible alias.\n- `sanitizeCommentBody()` keeps the known-local-token first pass, then delegates to `sanitizeOutput()` for secretlint/custom-pattern detection.\n- Added explicit dangerous flags: `--dangerously-skip-output-sanitization`, `--dangerously-skip-code-output-sanitization`, and `--dangerously-skip-active-tokens-output-sanitization`. Pattern sanitization can be skipped independently, but active local token masking remains enabled unless the active-token skip is explicitly set.\n- `src/tool-comments.lib.mjs#postTrackedComment` sanitizes controlled GitHub comment bodies before POSTing, so solve-owned comments get the same default protection as interactive-mode comments.\n\n**Defense layer 2 — interactive comment fix**\n- `src/interactive-mode.lib.mjs`: `postComment`/`editComment` run `sanitizeAndWarn()` on every body before it is queued or posted. Sanitization failure fails closed with `[redacted: sanitization failed]`.\n- `src/token-sanitization.lib.mjs`: `containsKnownToken()`, `getEnvironmentTokens()`, `getAllKnownLocalTokens()`, and `KNOWN_LOCAL_TOKEN_ENV_VARS` cover Telegram, gh, Claude, Codex/OpenAI, opencode, agent CLI, Gemini, Qwen, HuggingFace, and related local token env vars.\n\n**Defense layer 3 — static guardrails**\n- `eslint-rules/require-sanitized-output.mjs`: new custom ESLint rule that flags generated output passed directly to `gh pr comment`, `gh issue comment`, or PR body editing sinks unless it flows through `sanitizeOutput()`/compat aliases or a shared safe helper.\n- `eslint.config.mjs`: enables the rule in the existing lint suite.\n\n**Out-of-band owner notification**\n- `src/telegram-leak-notifier.lib.mjs`: callback-registry contract so the AI bridge can notify the bot without importing telegraf. `reportInteractiveLeak()` always succeeds and falls back to structured logging when no notifier is registered.\n- `src/telegram-bot.mjs`: registers a notifier on startup that DMs chat creators for allowlisted chats with masked token summaries.\n\n**Operator tooling — hidden `/tokens` command**\n- `src/telegram-tokens-command.lib.mjs`: private-chat only, owner-only (`getChatMember(...).status === 'creator'`), silently no-ops everywhere else. Output is always masked via `maskToken()`.\n\n**Mask format change**\n- `src/lib.mjs`: `maskToken()` defaults changed from 5+5 to 3+3 characters per issue requirements.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `node tests/test-token-leak-issue-1745.mjs` → 13/13\n- [x] `node tests/test-output-sanitization-options-1745.mjs` → 2/2\n- [x] `node tests/test-require-sanitized-output-rule.mjs`\n- [x] `node tests/test-token-sanitization.mjs` → 97/97\n- [x] `node tests/test-interactive-mode.mjs` → 111/111\n- [x] `npm run lint`\n- [x] `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs`\n- [x] `git diff --check`\n\nNote: local npm install warned that the package declares Node `>=24.0.0`; this workspace has Node `v20.20.2`. The targeted checks above still passed locally.\n\n## Case study\n\n`docs/case-studies/issue-1745/` contains the analysis, raw artifacts, and proposed long-term hardening plan requested by the issue.\n","created_at":"2026-05-02T19:30:43Z","updated_at":"2026-05-02T21:39:28Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T21:39:28Z","merged_at":"2026-05-02T21:39:28Z","merge_commit_sha":"8b687b48a20f318f2a4b4d50df1a95dae6c18d4c","assignees":[{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.