Docker Publish DinD (linux/arm64)	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-02T21:52:48.4969782Z               "message": "feat(security): wire sanitization stats, user-content carve-out, post-finish sweep (#1745)\n\nAddresses comment #4364642786 requirements:\n- Process-wide sanitization counters (totalMasked, knownTokenMasks,\n  patternMasks, hexMasks, excluded) with getSanitizationStats /\n  resetSanitizationStats / formatSanitizationSummary helpers; one-line\n  end-of-run summary printed in showSessionSummary with a hint to use\n  --dangerously-skip-output-sanitization when masking blocks workflow.\n- excludeTokens carve-out across sanitizeOutput and sanitizeCommentBody\n  so tokens already present in user-provided content stay visible while\n  active local tokens are still masked.\n- extractTokensFromUserContent helper extracts token-shaped strings from\n  user text and filters out known-active local tokens.\n- Post-finish sweep (runPostFinishSweep) re-reads bot-authored PR\n  conversation comments and the PR description after the AI session ends\n  and edits in place via gh api PATCH if a leak slipped past the live\n  sanitizer; gated by --dangerously-skip-output-sanitization /\n  --dangerously-skip-active-tokens-output-sanitization.\n- Skip flags plumbed through claude.lib, codex.lib, interactive-mode,\n  tool-comments so every comment-posting path honors them consistently.\n- Tests: tests/test-sanitization-stats-1745.mjs (11 passed) and\n  tests/test-post-finish-sweep-1745.mjs (4 passed) cover counters, the\n  carve-out, the end-of-run summary, and the retroactive sweep with a\n  fake \\$ supporting both tagged-template and options-then-tag forms.\n- Changeset updated with the comprehensive feature list.",
