Docker Publish (linux/arm64)	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-05-02T21:52:36.5477779Z               "message": "fix(security): sanitize interactive-mode comments to plug token leak (#1745)\n\nRoot cause: interactive-mode.lib.mjs#postComment / editComment posted raw\nBash tool output to GitHub without calling sanitizeLogContent. The leak in\nxlab2016/space_db_private#20 — TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN published in a public\nPR comment — flowed through this path. The pattern that would have caught\nit (telegram bot-token regex in detectSecretsWithCustomPatterns) was\nalready there but never invoked from the comment path.\n\nChanges:\n* maskToken() now defaults to first-3 + *** + last-3 (was 5+5) per the\n  issue requirement.\n* token-sanitization.lib.mjs adds a known-local-token registry covering\n  Telegram, GitHub, Claude, OpenAI/Codex, Gemini/Qwen, HuggingFace, and\n  the open-source agent CLIs. New helpers: getEnvironmentTokens(),\n  getAllKnownLocalTokens(), containsKnownToken(), sanitizeCommentBody().\n* interactive-mode.lib.mjs runs every outbound body through\n  sanitizeCommentBody() before posting/editing and fires a leak warning\n  via the telegram-leak-notifier when a known-local token was detected.\n* New telegram-leak-notifier.lib.mjs exposes a callback contract so the\n  bridge subprocess can DM the chat owner without depending on telegraf.\n* New telegram-tokens-command.lib.mjs implements a hidden /tokens command\n  (private DMs only, owner-only, undocumented, masked output).\n* telegram-bot.mjs registers /tokens and the leak-notifier callback that\n  DMs the creator of every allowlisted chat.\n\nSee docs/case-studies/issue-1745/analysis.md for the full timeline and\nroot-cause analysis.",
